    "body": "> > Currently, stakers with many validators cannot perform mass voluntary exits as the CLI command is interactive\r\n> \r\n> @rauljordan\r\n> What do you exactly mean by **many validators**? Many keys inside the same validator client or many validator clients each running one key or a few keys? There is one confirmation step for all keys combined.\r\n\r\nAs in having 32 ETH * 20 validators running on Prysm, on the same machine. \r\nSo I assume this would be _\"Many keys inside the same validator client\"_ :] Thats what I meant at least.\r\n\r\nSo basically **one command** to request exit for all validators at the same time. _Maximum_ a yes/no question but perhaps not even that. The ones who looks up and executes this command surely knows he is about to exit all validators wether its 1 x 32ETH or 500 x 32ETH instantly.\r\n\r\nMe myself will need the exit to be as easy as possible in case a family member for eg. need to exit on my behalf and dont feel comfy submitting commands in the terminal... Or have a cronjob that will exit in case i dont login into my server in a specific amount of time. So in that case it wont be slashing and slashing. A good feature imo :)",
